  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (950d863 2023-10-25T11:49:42.980532000Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge init\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nNone\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nThe changes in #5911 don't use the correct context for git fetch and uses it in the CWD. Should use the passed directory as the context for all git commands.\r\n\r\n```\r\n ~/empty\r\n$> forge init /Users/[user]/test --template immunefi-team/forge-poc-templates --branch default\r\nInitializing /Users/[user]/test from https://github.com/immunefi-team/forge-poc-templates...\r\nfatal: not a git repository (or any of the parent directories): .git\r\nError: \r\ngit fetch exited with code 128\r\n```",
